OL,3,GNorth East
OL,4,
OL,5,CThis Evening and Tonight:FSunny spells
OL,6,Fcontinue through the evening, though
OL,7,Fit will feel cool in a northerly
OL,8,Fbreeze. Largely dry overnight, with
OL,9,Fclear spells developing, although a
OL,10,Ffew isolated coastal showers are
OL,11,Flikely. Turning chilly with a fairly
OL,12,Fwidespread rural frost.
OL,13,
OL,14,CWednesday:FAfter a frosty start, sunny
OL,15,Fspells develop through the day.
OL,16,FLargely dry and cool, though isolated
OL,17,Fcoastal showers remain possible. Light
OL,18,Fwinds, with another frosty night to
OL,19,Fcome.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
